<p>The Bayway Isles and Isla del Sol neighborhoods feature newer construction with better insulation and more modern electrical systems, making them ideal candidates for larger solar installations and high-efficiency central HVAC systems. Downtown St Petersburg's growing condo market presents opportunities for shared solar installations and individual high-efficiency HVAC units. The Kenwood and Lakewood Estates neighborhoods, with their mid-century homes and larger lots, often accommodate ground-mounted solar arrays and whole-home HVAC upgrades that dramatically improve comfort and efficiency.</p>

